👉 **`this` means “this current object”**

### 🔹 Simple Example
class Student {
    String name;

    Student(String name) {
        this.name = name;
    }
}
```

👉 Here:

* `this.name` = **current object's name**
* It tells Java: “use the variable of this object”

---

### 🔹 Why we use `this`?

Because sometimes names are same:

```java
Student(String name) {
    this.name = name;
}
```

👉 Left side → object variable
👉 Right side → value coming in
